@TaylorPearsonMe Had this exact realization last week as well.

Honestly, one amazing byproduct of using CC more is that it forces me (w/ cc help) to create the robust documentation that used to be hard to justify the time for. 

And you're right, it compounds really quickly

@TaylorPearsonMe This is the sleeper feature.
End-of-session notes quietly turn work into a compounding system: memory, decisions, open loops.
At some point the tool isn’t assisting anymore — it’s running continuity for you.
